snippet.textDisplay:
I love this song.
The lyrics make me really sad even tho I haven't experienced anything like this by myself.
Like the ' your not the same' or 'your not the girl I fell in love with' makes me woahhh
(Just think, that this could be real: )
One side, it must be sad for Lauv, to see how the girl changed and you kind off fall out of love because she changes. This is frustrating isn't it?
Why does she change? Or more like how can I love her when she changes?
And on the other side the girl.
I mean couldn't it be that she changes naturally and that she so can't do anything against it and don't know what the problem is or how to fix it?
It must be horrible for her, when she is still in love with him, that she can't fix anything and don't know what is happening but still feels/ notices that something is changing? Like how the relationship, the atmosphere is slowly fading?
It's really frustrating for both sides I think.
The melody, the lyrics, the singers, the vocals. I love everything about it. A masterpiece
